$ ORACLE_HOME/OPatch

OPatch is Oracle's only supported method of installing *nterim → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/patching[patches]*. It updates
the central and per-product inventories with the details of the patch.

OPatch can only be used for OUI based → Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n[Oracle homes].

{ Files

  table { ll
    → Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/OPatch/datapatch[`datapatch`] ☰
    emdpatch.pl ☰
    → Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/OPatch/opatch[`opatch`] ☰ 
    opatch.pl ☰
    opatchauto ☰
    operr.bat ☰
    README.txt ☰
    version.txt ☰ contains the version number of OPatch, for example `12.2.0.1.15`
  table }

}
